# (resty) → R651 TS-Node=70 (got → Axis 16 1/1/1) → R652 95th
# language (Icon) → R653 Rust=71 (notify THIS — AXIS 17 OPENS) →
# expected R654 Go=71 → R655 TS-Node=71 → R656 96th language.
# This is the 1st of 3 leader bumps in the current segment.
#
# This completion OPENS Axis 17 (FILE WATCHING) — the 17th documented
# cross-language CLI library axis.  Axis 17 covers the cross-language
# pattern of "library used by CLIs to receive filesystem events"
# — applicable to hot-reloaders (cargo-watch, dprint, tobaru), code
# formatters (prettier --watch), build tools (webpack --watch,
# rollup --watch), and any CLI that responds to file changes.
#
#   Axis 17 (FILE WATCHING) variants:
#     - notify (notify-rs/notify) — R653 (THIS) — Rust cross-
#       platform filesystem events; inotify (Linux) + FSEvents
#       (macOS) + ReadDirectoryChangesW (Windows) + kqueue (BSD);
#       François Mockers / notify-rs ecosystem
#     - (Go variant pending in R654 — likely fsnotify/fsnotify,
#       the Go-equivalent cross-platform filesystem event library)
#     - (TS-Node variant pending in R655 — likely chokidar (paulmillr/
