# Axis 17 distribution: Rust=1, Go=0, TS-Node=0.  Will reach 1/1/1
# three-language symmetry by end of R655.
#
# Cross-language Axis 17 design analysis:
#   The "file watching" abstraction is non-stdlib in all three
#   languages — Rust's std::fs has no file-watching API; Go's
#   stdlib has no fsnotify equivalent (fsnotify is third-party);
#   Node.js's stdlib fs.watch IS available but unreliable across
#   platforms, so most production CLIs use chokidar.  Each
#   language's Axis 17 library wraps platform-specific kernel
#   APIs (inotify / FSEvents / ReadDirectoryChangesW / kqueue)
#   into a uniform cross-platform interface — a clean axis with
#   no stdlib overlap.
